description._content: ID: 064460 Title: Untitled. Provenance: 1780-1790 Caption: A bird's-eye view of the Red Fort at Delhi from the east, showing an emperor, probably Shah Alam (1759-1806) entering the Diwan-i-Khas on right. The Rang Mahal is on the left, the Khwabgah Jharoka in the centre and the Pearl Mosque on the extreme right Notes: Opaque watercolour.
